node.text: When you harbor negative emotions internally they’ll project themselves into the physical. When you internalize love, peace, harmony, & gratitude inside your external world will be filled with reasons to be happy and fulfilled. Be careful what you think about and the emotions you FEEL inside. Our internal world is merely a mirror of our physical world. Choose positive emotions and vibrations and you’ll attract the life you desire. #AM

node.title: Your outside world is a reflection of your inside world.

node.text:
⁣
Understand that in everyone’s lives there will be those “magical opportunities” where if you PUSH IT & really take advantage of it... you can set yourself up for the remainder of your life. ⁣
⁣
Personally, our company is THERE right now. I believe and know these next 24 months will be the 24 months we look back on and say, “That was the moment, the season, the time where people really focused and capitalized on the opportunity.”⁣
⁣
GO ALL IN. ⁣
Don’t play games. ⁣
Do whatever it takes.⁣
Vacation later.⁣
Mess around later.⁣
Do it NOW.⁣
⁣
See you at the top because the bottom is way too crowded. ⁣
⁣

node.text: #AM

node.title: On the days you don’t feel like doing it, do it anyway!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Alex Morton on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and indoor.

node.text:
⁣
Happy Sunday. Count your blessings today and be grateful for the people, health, love, success, opportunities, freedoms, & family in your life. ⁣
⁣
If you seek, you shall find reason(s) to be happy and grateful… life’s too short to be a miserable, negative, jealous, complaining, ungrateful, mean, blaming others, waste of a human life. ⁣It costs $0 to be a good person :) 
⁣
BE GREAT!! ⁣
⁣
-AM

node.text: We as humans will sabotage our own success by creating false beliefs in our minds and getting emotionally involved with the wrong ideas. We must plant the RIGHT IDEAS that will bring us closer to success and victory in our lives. #AM #Mentor

node.text:
⁣
Listen, if you’re blessed to still be a “young” aspiring entrepreneur take it from someone who’s been on the road since 2011 alllllll the way up to the first lockdown.. 70+ countries & lord knows how many miles… GO GET THE SUCCESS & GET IT DONE NOW. When you get engaged / married / have kids.. trust me.. the energy is different when it comes to “wanting to be on the road.” I just traveled for only 48 hours & the idea of being away from my fiancé any longer literally sucks.. cannot even fathom if we had kids right now. ⁣
⁣
When we’re 18-25 we think we have so much time and we do have so much time but seasons and priorities change. “Back in the day” I’d be on the road for 30-60 days straight and I was completely fine with it. Now today I’m over here doing 3 events and 2 countries in less than 48 hours so I can sleep in my own bed next to my person. My message is if you’re lucky enough to be involved in a business where financial freedom is attainable AND not yet starting a family you should be working 17-20 hours a day, 7 days a week, to get it completely done. So when you do settle down, have kids, you’re not FORCED to “hit the road” whatsoever. Take this anyway you want, not trying to offend anyone.. but you don’t want to be doing red eye flights at 40 out of financial desperation. Then again this is just my opinion. ⁣
⁣
Burn the midnight oil now, sacrifice the ‘fun’ now, work your face off now, go all in now, so you can have total freedom later… I remember years ago thinking to myself that one day all the work will be worth it when I’m one of the only dads picking up their kids at school. When my mom would pick up Maddie and I it was 99.999% moms picking up their kids because the dads were at work, and nothings wrong with that. But I always told myself that wouldn’t be my future. In 2011 I made the decision to do 40 years of work and results in way under half the time.⁣
⁣
DECIDE / COMMIT / GO HARD. ⁣
⁣
#AM

node.text: You can’t go through life getting offended by what people say or think about you. WHO CARES. Stop being sensitive about success. If you want success you need to go out and TAKE IT! Nobody is going to serve success up to you on a silver platter. Stop being sensitive and scared… GO TAKE IT & be willing to go through the pain!! #AM

node.text: Took a red eye flight last night from LA to Atlanta, didn’t sleep a wink. Landed and went to speak to 1000’s, went back to the ✈️, flew 2.5 hours to Monterrey, went directly to another packed out venue &  educated for a hour.. & now as I’m writing this heading back to the plane heading to the next city for tomorrow’s event. WORK ETHIC is something you just can’t talk about but you’ve got to be about. NEXT LEVEL everything.. grateful to GOD I still get to do what I love everyday almost 11 years later. AMAZING ENERGY TODAY!!! #AM #MissingMyFiance

node.text: We all want better friendships, the perfect relationship, more money, better health, a more desirable life… except we’re operating with the wrong programming and continually getting the same results (we don’t want) over and over again. If your way isn’t working, try this way. Attempt to re program your mind with the RIGHT THINKING, feelings, & massive action. For things to CHANGE, you must CHANGE. #AM

node.text:
⁣
Decided to go have a picnic through @thepicnic.collective yesterday & go ride the carnival rides like little kids at Santa Monica Pier. Why? Because we are free. When you’re free you can do whatever you want. Freedom is very important, for many reasons.. however true freedom requires sacrifice, hard work, & dedication. ⁣
⁣
When I was 18 I made a decision that I was going to work hard and make it happen. Growing up I saw my friends parents stressed about money, listened to conversations about the lack of money and I could easily see the frustration and negative emotions associated with having “less than enough.” I told myself I would never go through that. I always knew I’d get married, start a family, and when that time would come I always knew I would’ve already accomplished enough so my wife and kids wouldn’t need to worry or be stressed out. ⁣
⁣
Money effects every decision. Where you buy groceries to feed your family. Organic and fresh or processed crap. Where you live? A private and secure neighborhood or completely exposed to the outside world. What kind of school will your kids attend? We want our kids to speak English, Spanish, Mandarin, & Arabic fluently at a bare minimum. It’s a global marketplace. Simply English they’ll be slaughtered. When you take vacations where will you stay? Where will you go? How cultured will your children be, what will their world scope entail?⁣ Kids subconscious minds are 95% programmed prior to their teenage years. 
⁣
You see. Most people don’t plan their lives and then wake up in their 40’s unhappy, depressed, & have less than enough. It’s nobody’s fault but their own. This may sound harsh or you might be saying “easy for you to say man.. “kid who grew up with both parents, went to college… bla bla”. That’s your limiting beliefs and poor paradigm kicking in. Plus I work with individuals who had it wayyyyyyy worse than you, trust me. ⁣Reasons and excuses are the same thing. 
⁣
Anyway, FREEDOM is important. Financial independence is important. & it’s never too late. ⁣
Keep fighting for your dreams. I believe in you!!! By the way the best thing I ever did was somehow get this woman to fall in love with me. #AM
